analysis.Summary: Vue component that renders an SVG icon representing an order status of “Created.” It displays a circular outline filled with a configurable color.
analysis.Purpose: Provides a reusable, presentational icon for the “Created” state in the orders module of the application.

Components.name: IconStatusCreated
responsibilities: Accept a fill color via props

Functions.name: defineProps
Functions.purpose: Declare component props in script setup syntax

Dependencies: Global CSS variables (e.g. --black) for default coloring
analysis.Usage:
Import and register or use directly in a parent Vue component:

import IconStatusCreated from 'modules/orders/components/icons/IconStatusCreated.vue';

<template>
  <IconStatusCreated fill="#4caf50" />
</template>
Notes: No <style> block—styles are driven entirely by the SVG and CSS variables.
Purely presentational; contains no event handlers or reactive state.
Lightweight and easily themeable via the `fill` prop.
